How do you align a row of divs to the right using flex in css?  Show me an example.
Sure, here's how you can use CSS Flexbox to align rows of `div` elements horizontally and set their width based on content inside them:
```css
/* Set up container with a fixed height */
#container {
  display: flex; /* enable horizontal layout using flexbox */
  justify-content: space-between; /* distribute items evenly along the row, leaving gaps for spacing between elements */
  align-items: center; /* vertically center all items in each column */
  width: 800px; /* set a fixed container width to accommodate your content */
}
```
Then you can add `divs` inside this container with their respective classes and styles, like so:
```css
/* Add div elements for the first row of text */
.row1 {
  display: flex; /* enable horizontal layout using flexbox */
  justify-content: space-between; /* distribute items evenly along the row, leaving gaps for spacing between elements */
}

#container .row1 > * {
  width: 50%; /* set a fixed width of each item in this column to accommodate your content */
}
```
And finally you can add more rows with their respective classes and styles.
